d=3D"173">Got it. This is a <strong data-start=3D"18" data-end=3D"61">=E2=
=80=9CPR stack generator + stack maintainer=E2=80=9D</strong> for strict-re=
view orgs, with one hard constraint: <strong data-start=3D"112" data-end=3D=
"173">never change semantics unless a reviewer explicitly asks.</strong></p=
>
<h2 data-start=3D"175" data-end=3D"228">Where to start (because =E2=80=9Cal=
l types=E2=80=9D will kill you)</h2>
<p data-start=3D"229" data-end=3D"258">Easiest first, hardest later:</p>
<ol data-start=3D"260" data-end=3D"308">
<li data-start=3D"260" data-end=3D"308">
<p data-start=3D"263" data-end=3D"308"><strong data-start=3D"263" data-end=
=3D"308">Backend services / libraries (best wedge)</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"309" data-end=3D"447">
<li data-start=3D"309" data-end=3D"368">
<p data-start=3D"311" data-end=3D"368">Clear layering (types =E2=86=92 core=
 logic =E2=86=92 API wiring =E2=86=92 tests).</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"369" data-end=3D"400">
<p data-start=3D"371" data-end=3D"400">Less churn from CSS/UI noise.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"401" data-end=3D"447">
<p data-start=3D"403" data-end=3D"447">Tests are easier to use as acceptanc=
e gates.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"2" data-start=3D"449" data-end=3D"477">
<li data-start=3D"449" data-end=3D"477">
<p data-start=3D"452" data-end=3D"477"><strong data-start=3D"452" data-end=
=3D"477">Infra (Terraform/K8s)</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"478" data-end=3D"588">
<li data-start=3D"478" data-end=3D"557">
<p data-start=3D"480" data-end=3D"557">Can be sliceable (modules, envs), bu=
t reviewers often demand =E2=80=9Catomic safety=E2=80=9D.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"558" data-end=3D"588">
<p data-start=3D"560" data-end=3D"588">Drift/conflicts are painful.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"3" data-start=3D"590" data-end=3D"626">
<li data-start=3D"590" data-end=3D"626">
<p data-start=3D"593" data-end=3D"626"><strong data-start=3D"593" data-end=
=3D"626">Full-stack web apps (hardest)</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"627" data-end=3D"708">
<li data-start=3D"627" data-end=3D"708">
<p data-start=3D"629" data-end=3D"708">UI churn, file scatter, =E2=80=9Ctou=
ch everything=E2=80=9D changes, golden tests often missing.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"710" data-end=3D"811">So: <strong data-start=3D"714" data-=
end=3D"754">start with backend + libs on GitHub.</strong> Keep =E2=80=9Cweb=
 app=E2=80=9D as a later vertical once slicing is good.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"813" data-end=3D"877">Feature flags: why they help review=
 (and when they=E2=80=99re poison)</h2>
<p data-start=3D"878" data-end=3D"983">Feature flags help because they let =
you split =E2=80=9Cscaffolding=E2=80=9D from =E2=80=9Cbehavior change=E2=80=
=9D without breaking main:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"984" data-end=3D"1211">
<li data-start=3D"984" data-end=3D"1066">
<p data-start=3D"986" data-end=3D"1066">PR1 adds plumbing + flag default OF=
F =E2=86=92 reviewers can approve low-risk structure.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1067" data-end=3D"1136">
<p data-start=3D"1069" data-end=3D"1136">PR2 implements behavior behind the=
 flag =E2=86=92 reviewers focus on logic.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1137" data-end=3D"1211">
<p data-start=3D"1139" data-end=3D"1211">PR3 flips flag or enables in confi=
g (often last, or never auto-flipped).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1213" data-end=3D"1256">But in strict cultures, flags are =
hated if:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"1257" data-end=3D"1359">
<li data-start=3D"1257" data-end=3D"1288">
<p data-start=3D"1259" data-end=3D"1288">They add permanent complexity</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1289" data-end=3D"1334">
<p data-start=3D"1291" data-end=3D"1334">They=E2=80=99re used to smuggle ha=
lf-baked behavior</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1335" data-end=3D"1359">
<p data-start=3D"1337" data-end=3D"1359">They=E2=80=99re not cleaned up</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1361" data-end=3D"1414">So treat flags as <strong data-sta=
rt=3D"1379" data-end=3D"1391">optional</strong> and <strong data-start=3D"1=
396" data-end=3D"1413">policy-driven</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"1415" data-end=3D"1489">
<li data-start=3D"1415" data-end=3D"1489">
<p data-start=3D"1417" data-end=3D"1489">Repo policy: =E2=80=9Cflags allowe=
d only if removed within N PRs=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cno flags=E2=80=9D.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start=3D"1491" data-end=3D"1556">What to prioritize (you <em data-=
start=3D"1518" data-end=3D"1524">must</em> pick, even if you =E2=80=9Cdon=
=E2=80=99t know=E2=80=9D)</h2>
<p data-start=3D"1557" data-end=3D"1634">Your users said it for you: strict=
 reviewers want <strong data-start=3D"1607" data-end=3D"1633">reviewability=
 + safety</strong>.</p>
<p data-start=3D"1636" data-end=3D"1652">So optimize for:</p>
<ol data-start=3D"1653" data-end=3D"1878">
<li data-start=3D"1653" data-end=3D"1730">
<p data-start=3D"1656" data-end=3D"1730"><strong data-start=3D"1656" data-e=
nd=3D"1692">Each PR is reviewable on its own</strong> (small, coherent, min=
imal diff noise)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1731" data-end=3D"1802">
<p data-start=3D"1734" data-end=3D"1802"><strong data-start=3D"1734" data-e=
nd=3D"1758">Each PR is mergeable</strong> (builds/tests pass or is explicit=
ly exempt)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1803" data-end=3D"1878">
<p data-start=3D"1806" data-end=3D"1878"><strong data-start=3D"1806" data-e=
nd=3D"1839">Downstream churn is minimized</strong> (stable stacks, no const=
ant re-review)</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start=3D"1880" data-end=3D"1908">Speed-to-merge is secondary.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"1910" data-end=3D"1951">Acceptance test: do this pragmati=
cally</h2>
<p data-start=3D"1952" data-end=3D"2041">You don=E2=80=99t want the tool in=
venting tests or =E2=80=9Cfixing=E2=80=9D behavior. So make acceptance laye=
red:</p>
<p data-start=3D"2043" data-end=3D"2064"><strong data-start=3D"2043" data-e=
nd=3D"2064">Minimum (always):</strong></p>
<ul data-start=3D"2065" data-end=3D"2129">
<li data-start=3D"2065" data-end=3D"2112">
<p data-start=3D"2067" data-end=3D"2112"><code data-start=3D"2067" data-end=
=3D"2098">lint + typecheck + unit tests</code> if they exist</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2113" data-end=3D"2129">
<p data-start=3D"2115" data-end=3D"2129">Build succeeds</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"2131" data-end=3D"2159"><strong data-start=3D"2131" data-e=
nd=3D"2159">Better (if repo has it):</strong></p>
<ul data-start=3D"2160" data-end=3D"2194">
<li data-start=3D"2160" data-end=3D"2194">
<p data-start=3D"2162" data-end=3D"2194">existing e2e / integration suite</=
p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"2196" data-end=3D"2233"><strong data-start=3D"2196" data-e=
nd=3D"2233">Fallback (when repo has nothing):</strong></p>
<ul data-start=3D"2234" data-end=3D"2413">
<li data-start=3D"2234" data-end=3D"2297">
<p data-start=3D"2236" data-end=3D"2297">=E2=80=9Csmoke command=E2=80=9D de=
clared by repo: <code data-start=3D"2270" data-end=3D"2297">make dev &amp;&=
amp; curl /healthz</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2298" data-end=3D"2413">
<p data-start=3D"2300" data-end=3D"2413">If even that doesn=E2=80=99t exist=
, you can=E2=80=99t guarantee anything=E2=80=94so you label PRs with =E2=80=
=9CNo automated acceptance in repo=E2=80=9D.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"2415" data-end=3D"2502">Key point: the tool should require=
 the repo to declare <em data-start=3D"2470" data-end=3D"2490">what =E2=80=
=9Cworks=E2=80=9D means</em>, not guess.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"2504" data-end=3D"2561">Core workflow on <span class=3D"h=
over:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><=
span class=3D"whitespace-normal">GitHub</span></span></h2>
<h3 data-start=3D"2562" data-end=3D"2572">Inputs</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"2573" data-end=3D"2725">
<li data-start=3D"2573" data-end=3D"2598">
<p data-start=3D"2575" data-end=3D"2598">Big diff (branch or PR)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2599" data-end=3D"2635">
<p data-start=3D"2601" data-end=3D"2635">Full chat transcript (plan/intent)=
</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2636" data-end=3D"2684">
<p data-start=3D"2638" data-end=3D"2684">Repo metadata (languages, test com=
mands, lint)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2685" data-end=3D"2725">
<p data-start=3D"2687" data-end=3D"2725">Optional: CODEOWNERS + paths owner=
ship</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"2727" data-end=3D"2757">Output: generated PR stack</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"2758" data-end=3D"2977">
<li data-start=3D"2758" data-end=3D"2811">
<p data-start=3D"2760" data-end=3D"2811">Creates branches <code data-start=
=3D"2777" data-end=3D"2790">stack/001-=E2=80=A6</code>, <code data-start=3D=
"2792" data-end=3D"2805">stack/002-=E2=80=A6</code>, etc.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2812" data-end=3D"2850">
<p data-start=3D"2814" data-end=3D"2850">Creates PRs as <strong data-start=
=3D"2829" data-end=3D"2838">Draft</strong> by default.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2851" data-end=3D"2977">
<p data-start=3D"2853" data-end=3D"2870">Each PR includes:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"2873" data-end=3D"2977">
<li data-start=3D"2873" data-end=3D"2894">
<p data-start=3D"2875" data-end=3D"2894">Summary, motivation</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2897" data-end=3D"2914">
<p data-start=3D"2899" data-end=3D"2914">=E2=80=9CDepends on #X=E2=80=9D</p=
>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2917" data-end=3D"2948">
<p data-start=3D"2919" data-end=3D"2948">What reviewers should look at</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2951" data-end=3D"2977">
<p data-start=3D"2953" data-end=3D"2977">Test status + how to run</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"2979" data-end=3D"3003">After review on PR i</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"3004" data-end=3D"3246">
<li data-start=3D"3004" data-end=3D"3050">
<p data-start=3D"3006" data-end=3D"3050">Vibe coder applies requested chang=
es on PR i</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3051" data-end=3D"3246">
<p data-start=3D"3053" data-end=3D"3063">Tool then:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"3066" data-end=3D"3246">
<li data-start=3D"3066" data-end=3D"3085">
<p data-start=3D"3068" data-end=3D"3085">Rebases PR i+1..n</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3088" data-end=3D"3146">
<p data-start=3D"3090" data-end=3D"3146">Resolves conflicts <em data-start=
=3D"3109" data-end=3D"3123">mechanically</em> (no semantic rewrites)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3149" data-end=3D"3182">
<p data-start=3D"3151" data-end=3D"3182">Re-runs checks for affected PRs</p=
>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3185" data-end=3D"3246">
<p data-start=3D"3187" data-end=3D"3246">Updates PR descriptions with =E2=
=80=9Cchanged since last review: =E2=80=A6=E2=80=9D</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"3248" data-end=3D"3278">=E2=80=9CReviewer denied=E2=80=9D=
 handling</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"3279" data-end=3D"3581">
<li data-start=3D"3279" data-end=3D"3581">
<p data-start=3D"3281" data-end=3D"3311">If reviewer says =E2=80=9Cdon=E2=
=80=99t do X=E2=80=9D:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"3314" data-end=3D"3581">
<li data-start=3D"3314" data-end=3D"3363">
<p data-start=3D"3316" data-end=3D"3363">Tool finds downstream references t=
hat rely on X</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3366" data-end=3D"3524">
<p data-start=3D"3368" data-end=3D"3409">Opens a =E2=80=9Crepair plan=E2=80=
=9D for the vibe coder:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"3414" data-end=3D"3524">
<li data-start=3D"3414" data-end=3D"3438">
<p data-start=3D"3416" data-end=3D"3438">Option A: remove usage</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3443" data-end=3D"3473">
<p data-start=3D"3445" data-end=3D"3473">Option B: alternate approach</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3478" data-end=3D"3524">
<p data-start=3D"3480" data-end=3D"3524">Option C: keep but feature-flag (i=
f allowed)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3527" data-end=3D"3581">
<p data-start=3D"3529" data-end=3D"3581">The coder picks. Tool applies mech=
anical edits only.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start=3D"3583" data-end=3D"3632">The real product trick: how you s=
plit the diff</h2>
<p data-start=3D"3633" data-end=3D"3686">You need a slicing engine that use=
s multiple signals:</p>
<ol data-start=3D"3688" data-end=3D"3711">
<li data-start=3D"3688" data-end=3D"3711">
<p data-start=3D"3691" data-end=3D"3711"><strong data-start=3D"3691" data-e=
nd=3D"3711">Dependency graph</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"3712" data-end=3D"3753">
<li data-start=3D"3712" data-end=3D"3753">
<p data-start=3D"3714" data-end=3D"3753">imports, symbols, DB schema, API r=
outes</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"2" data-start=3D"3754" data-end=3D"3783">
<li data-start=3D"3754" data-end=3D"3783">
<p data-start=3D"3757" data-end=3D"3783"><strong data-start=3D"3757" data-e=
nd=3D"3783">Intent from transcript</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"3784" data-end=3D"3824">
<li data-start=3D"3784" data-end=3D"3824">
<p data-start=3D"3786" data-end=3D"3824">map =E2=80=9Cwhat user meant=E2=80=
=9D to files/touches</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"3" data-start=3D"3825" data-end=3D"3853">
<li data-start=3D"3825" data-end=3D"3853">
<p data-start=3D"3828" data-end=3D"3853"><strong data-start=3D"3828" data-e=
nd=3D"3853">Change classification</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"3854" data-end=3D"3903">
<li data-start=3D"3854" data-end=3D"3903">
<p data-start=3D"3856" data-end=3D"3903">formatting/refactor vs feature vs =
tests vs docs</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"4" data-start=3D"3904" data-end=3D"3929">
<li data-start=3D"3904" data-end=3D"3929">
<p data-start=3D"3907" data-end=3D"3929"><strong data-start=3D"3907" data-e=
nd=3D"3929">Policy constraints</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"3930" data-end=3D"4015">
<li data-start=3D"3930" data-end=3D"3970">
<p data-start=3D"3932" data-end=3D"3970">=E2=80=9Ctests must be in same PR =
as behavior=E2=80=9D</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3971" data-end=3D"3983">
<p data-start=3D"3973" data-end=3D"3983">=E2=80=9Cno flags=E2=80=9D</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3984" data-end=3D"4015">
<p data-start=3D"3986" data-end=3D"4015">=E2=80=9Cmigrations must be isolat=
ed=E2=80=9D</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"4017" data-end=3D"4072">Then you generate an <strong data-=
start=3D"4038" data-end=3D"4055">ordered stack</strong> with rules like:</p=
>
<ul data-start=3D"4073" data-end=3D"4211">
<li data-start=3D"4073" data-end=3D"4116">
<p data-start=3D"4075" data-end=3D"4116">=E2=80=9CTypes/interfaces before i=
mplementations=E2=80=9D</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"4117" data-end=3D"4162">
<p data-start=3D"4119" data-end=3D"4162">=E2=80=9CPure refactors before beh=
avior=E2=80=9D (optional)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"4163" data-end=3D"4197">
<p data-start=3D"4165" data-end=3D"4197">=E2=80=9CWiring/config after core =
logic=E2=80=9D</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"4198" data-end=3D"4211">
<p data-start=3D"4200" data-end=3D"4211">=E2=80=9CDocs last=E2=80=9D</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start=3D"4213" data-end=3D"4259">What =E2=80=9Cstack PR reviews=E2=
=80=9D implies (important)</h2>
<p data-start=3D"4260" data-end=3D"4315">Strict orgs often <em data-start=
=3D"4278" data-end=3D"4284">hate</em> stacked PRs because they fear:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"4316" data-end=3D"4377">
<li data-start=3D"4316" data-end=3D"4355">
<p data-start=3D"4318" data-end=3D"4355">reviewing code that isn=E2=80=99t =
on main yet</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"4356" data-end=3D"4377">
<p data-start=3D"4358" data-end=3D"4377">review invalidation</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"4379" data-end=3D"4391">So you need:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"4392" data-end=3D"4613">
<li data-start=3D"4392" data-end=3D"4457">
<p data-start=3D"4394" data-end=3D"4457">Clear =E2=80=9Cdiff base=E2=80=9D =
UX: show PR diff against its parent, not main</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"4458" data-end=3D"4528">
<p data-start=3D"4460" data-end=3D"4528">A =E2=80=9Cstack view=E2=80=9D das=
hboard: status per PR (checks, approvals, blocked)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"4529" data-end=3D"4565">
<p data-start=3D"4531" data-end=3D"4565">Stable links + stable PR numbering=
</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"4566" data-end=3D"4613">
<p data-start=3D"4568" data-end=3D"4613">Minimal rebases (batch updates whe=
n possible)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start=3D"4615" data-end=3D"4655">MVP that can win in enterprises /=
 OSS</h2>
<p data-start=3D"4656" data-end=3D"4807"><strong data-start=3D"4656" data-e=
nd=3D"4734">MVP =3D split a giant PR into 4=E2=80=938 draft PRs + maintain =
the stack via rebase.</strong><br>
No fancy auto-fixes. No invented tests. No rewriting code =E2=80=9Cfor qual=
ity=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p data-start=3D"4809" data-end=3D"4893">If you can do that reliably for 1=
=E2=80=932 languages (say TS + Python), you have a product.</p>
<hr data-start=3D"4895" data-end=3D"4898">
<h2 data-start=3D"4900" data-end=3D"4934">Questions (tight, but decisive)</=
h2>
<ol data-start=3D"4935" data-end=3D"5379">
<li data-start=3D"4935" data-end=3D"5001">
<p data-start=3D"4938" data-end=3D"5001"><strong data-start=3D"4938" data-e=
nd=3D"4956">Max stack size</strong> you think reviewers will tolerate: 3? 5=
? 10?</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"5002" data-end=3D"5174">
<p data-start=3D"5005" data-end=3D"5174">In strict culture, is it acceptabl=
e that intermediate PRs are =E2=80=9Cmergeable but incomplete=E2=80=9D (e.g=
., adds types but no behavior), or must every PR produce user-visible value=
?</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"5175" data-end=3D"5260">
<p data-start=3D"5178" data-end=3D"5260">Do you want to enforce =E2=80=9Cte=
sts must ship with behavior PR=E2=80=9D, or allow =E2=80=9Ctests later=E2=
=80=9D?</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"5261" data-end=3D"5379">
<p data-start=3D"5264" data-end=3D"5379">How should it behave when the tran=
script intent conflicts with code diff (coder drifted)? Trust code or trans=
cript?</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start=3D"5381" data-end=3D"5411">Answer those and I=E2=80=99ll prop=
ose:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"5412" data-end=3D"5588" data-is-last-node=3D"" data-is-on=
ly-node=3D"">
<li data-start=3D"5412" data-end=3D"5463">
<p data-start=3D"5414" data-end=3D"5463">a concrete slicing strategy (rules=
 + heuristics),</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"5464" data-end=3D"5483">
<p data-start=3D"5466" data-end=3D"5483">the PR templates,</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"5484" data-end=3D"5588" data-is-last-node=3D"">
<p data-start=3D"5486" data-end=3D"5588" data-is-last-node=3D"">and an init=
ial architecture (repo analyzer + stack planner + GitHub PR orchestrator + =
rebase manager).</p>
</li>
