-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-styling"><h3 data-start=3D=
"0" data-end=3D"57">What usually happens with stacked PRs + feature flags</=
h3>
<p data-start=3D"58" data-end=3D"102">In strict-review orgs you=E2=80=99ll =
see 3 patterns:</p>
<ol data-start=3D"104" data-end=3D"156">
<li data-start=3D"104" data-end=3D"156">
<p data-start=3D"107" data-end=3D"156"><strong data-start=3D"107" data-end=
=3D"156">Flag as a =E2=80=9Cstack enabler=E2=80=9D (common, tolerated)</str=
ong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"157" data-end=3D"421">
<li data-start=3D"157" data-end=3D"214">
<p data-start=3D"159" data-end=3D"214">PR1: plumbing + flag default OFF (no=
 behavior change)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"215" data-end=3D"261">
<p data-start=3D"217" data-end=3D"261">PR2: full behavior behind flag (stil=
l OFF)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"262" data-end=3D"421">
<p data-start=3D"264" data-end=3D"421">PR3: flip flag / remove old path (of=
ten later, sometimes separate rollout)<br>
Why reviewers like it: they can approve structure without worrying you brok=
e prod.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"2" data-start=3D"423" data-end=3D"475">
<li data-start=3D"423" data-end=3D"475">
<p data-start=3D"426" data-end=3D"475"><strong data-start=3D"426" data-end=
=3D"475">Flags banned, stacks still used (also common)</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"476" data-end=3D"676">
<li data-start=3D"476" data-end=3D"676">
<p data-start=3D"478" data-end=3D"676">Teams insist every PR is safe <em da=
ta-start=3D"508" data-end=3D"523">without flags</em>: compile + tests + no =
partial behavior.<br>
This forces the stack to be sliced along =E2=80=9Ccomplete vertical slices=
=E2=80=9D (small end-to-end increments), not =E2=80=9Clayers=E2=80=9D.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"3" data-start=3D"678" data-end=3D"719">
<li data-start=3D"678" data-end=3D"719">
<p data-start=3D"681" data-end=3D"719"><strong data-start=3D"681" data-end=
=3D"719">Flags abused (what reviewers hate)</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"720" data-end=3D"877">
<li data-start=3D"720" data-end=3D"779">
<p data-start=3D"722" data-end=3D"779">Half-implemented behavior hidden beh=
ind flags for months.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"780" data-end=3D"798">
<p data-start=3D"782" data-end=3D"798">No cleanup plan.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"799" data-end=3D"877">
<p data-start=3D"801" data-end=3D"877">Branching logic everywhere.<br>
Result: reviewers start blocking flags entirely.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"879" data-end=3D"971">So the =E2=80=9Cusual=E2=80=9D is: f=
lags are a tool to keep intermediate PRs safe, but they need <strong data-s=
tart=3D"960" data-end=3D"970">policy</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"972" data-end=3D"1089">
<li data-start=3D"972" data-end=3D"1011">
<p data-start=3D"974" data-end=3D"1011">allowed only with expiry / cleanup =
PR</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1012" data-end=3D"1040">
<p data-start=3D"1014" data-end=3D"1040">centralized flag framework</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1041" data-end=3D"1089">
<p data-start=3D"1043" data-end=3D"1089">require tests for both paths (ofte=
n too heavy)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1091" data-end=3D"1148"><strong data-start=3D"1091" data-e=
nd=3D"1137">Your tool should not decide this globally.</strong> It should:<=
/p>
<ul data-start=3D"1149" data-end=3D"1285">
<li data-start=3D"1149" data-end=3D"1178">
<p data-start=3D"1151" data-end=3D"1178">detect repo policy (config)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1179" data-end=3D"1236">
<p data-start=3D"1181" data-end=3D"1236">propose flag use only when needed =
to keep PRs mergeable</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1237" data-end=3D"1285">
<p data-start=3D"1239" data-end=3D"1285">enforce =E2=80=9Cflag removal PR=
=E2=80=9D if flags are allowed</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start=3D"1287" data-end=3D"1290">
<h2 data-start=3D"1292" data-end=3D"1363">Since you don=E2=80=99t know max =
stack size / PR completeness, pick defaults</h2>
<p data-start=3D"1364" data-end=3D"1403">You need defaults or you=E2=80=99l=
l never ship.</p>
<p data-start=3D"1405" data-end=3D"1441"><strong data-start=3D"1405" data-e=
nd=3D"1441">Default A (enterprise-friendly):</strong></p>
<ul data-start=3D"1442" data-end=3D"1657">
<li data-start=3D"1442" data-end=3D"1488">
<p data-start=3D"1444" data-end=3D"1488">Stack size target: <strong data-st=
art=3D"1463" data-end=3D"1472">5 PRs</strong>, hard cap <strong data-start=
=3D"1483" data-end=3D"1488">8</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1489" data-end=3D"1528">
<p data-start=3D"1491" data-end=3D"1528">No PR is allowed to break build/te=
sts</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1529" data-end=3D"1602">
<p data-start=3D"1531" data-end=3D"1602">Flags: <strong data-start=3D"1538"=
 data-end=3D"1556">off by default</strong>, only if needed to keep intermed=
iate PRs safe</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1603" data-end=3D"1657">
<p data-start=3D"1605" data-end=3D"1657">Tests must land with the PR that i=
ntroduces behavior</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1659" data-end=3D"1725">Rationale: reviewers tolerate 4=E2=
=80=936. Beyond that they lose the plot.</p>
<hr data-start=3D"1727" data-end=3D"1730">
<h2 data-start=3D"1732" data-end=3D"1795">Trust code over transcript: conse=
quences (good choice, but=E2=80=A6)</h2>
<p data-start=3D"1796" data-end=3D"1840">If transcript is optional and code=
 is truth:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"1841" data-end=3D"1970">
<li data-start=3D"1841" data-end=3D"1905">
<p data-start=3D"1843" data-end=3D"1905">transcript becomes a <strong data-=
start=3D"1864" data-end=3D"1885">hint for ordering</strong> and PR descript=
ions</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1906" data-end=3D"1970">
<p data-start=3D"1908" data-end=3D"1970">the tool must never =E2=80=9Ccorre=
ct=E2=80=9D the diff to match the transcript</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1972" data-end=3D"2008">So transcript is: =E2=80=9Cwhy=E2=
=80=9D, not =E2=80=9Cwhat=E2=80=9D.</p>
<hr data-start=3D"2010" data-end=3D"2013">
<h2 data-start=3D"2015" data-end=3D"2074">What I=E2=80=99d build as the fir=
st slicing algorithm (concrete)</h2>
<p data-start=3D"2075" data-end=3D"2135">Given a big diff, produce 3=E2=80=
=937 PRs via deterministic buckets:</p>
<ol data-start=3D"2137" data-end=3D"2193">
<li data-start=3D"2137" data-end=3D"2193">
<p data-start=3D"2140" data-end=3D"2193"><strong data-start=3D"2140" data-e=
nd=3D"2169">Mechanical / non-semantic</strong> (optional, default OFF)</p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"2194" data-end=3D"2305">
<li data-start=3D"2194" data-end=3D"2305">
<p data-start=3D"2196" data-end=3D"2305">formatting, renames, lint-only cha=
nges<br data-start=3D"2234" data-end=3D"2237">
(Only do this if you can prove no behavior changes; otherwise skip.)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"2" data-start=3D"2307" data-end=3D"2333">
<li data-start=3D"2307" data-end=3D"2333">
<p data-start=3D"2310" data-end=3D"2333"><strong data-start=3D"2310" data-e=
nd=3D"2333">Contracts / schemas</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"2334" data-end=3D"2403">
<li data-start=3D"2334" data-end=3D"2403">
<p data-start=3D"2336" data-end=3D"2403">types, interfaces, protobuf/openap=
i, DB migrations (often isolated)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"3" data-start=3D"2405" data-end=3D"2431">
<li data-start=3D"2405" data-end=3D"2431">
<p data-start=3D"2408" data-end=3D"2431"><strong data-start=3D"2408" data-e=
nd=3D"2431">Core implementation</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"2432" data-end=3D"2472">
<li data-start=3D"2432" data-end=3D"2472">
<p data-start=3D"2434" data-end=3D"2472">business logic, libs, internal mod=
ules</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"4" data-start=3D"2474" data-end=3D"2501">
<li data-start=3D"2474" data-end=3D"2501">
<p data-start=3D"2477" data-end=3D"2501"><strong data-start=3D"2477" data-e=
nd=3D"2501">Integration / wiring</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"2502" data-end=3D"2544">
<li data-start=3D"2502" data-end=3D"2544">
<p data-start=3D"2504" data-end=3D"2544">routes, DI, config, feature regist=
ration</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"5" data-start=3D"2546" data-end=3D"2558">
<li data-start=3D"2546" data-end=3D"2558">
<p data-start=3D"2549" data-end=3D"2558"><strong data-start=3D"2549" data-e=
nd=3D"2558">Tests</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"2559" data-end=3D"2640">
<li data-start=3D"2559" data-end=3D"2640">
<p data-start=3D"2561" data-end=3D"2640">unit + integration tests for new b=
ehavior (paired with #3/#4 if policy demands)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"6" data-start=3D"2642" data-end=3D"2664">
<li data-start=3D"2642" data-end=3D"2664">
<p data-start=3D"2645" data-end=3D"2664"><strong data-start=3D"2645" data-e=
nd=3D"2664">Docs / examples</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"2665" data-end=3D"2691">
<li data-start=3D"2665" data-end=3D"2691">
<p data-start=3D"2667" data-end=3D"2691">README, usage, changelog</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"2693" data-end=3D"2809">Then order them by dependency (imp=
orts/symbol references) and cap to 5=E2=80=938 PRs by merging adjacent buck=
ets when small.</p>
<hr data-start=3D"2811" data-end=3D"2814">
<h2 data-start=3D"2816" data-end=3D"2857">The product decision you must mak=
e now</h2>
<p data-start=3D"2858" data-end=3D"2899">When you =E2=80=9Cdissect=E2=80=9D=
 a big PR, do you want:</p>
<h3 data-start=3D"2901" data-end=3D"2955">Option 1: <strong data-start=3D"2=
915" data-end=3D"2933">Layered stacks</strong> (fastest to generate)</h3>
<p data-start=3D"2956" data-end=3D"3080">Contracts =E2=86=92 core =E2=86=92=
 wiring =E2=86=92 tests<br data-start=3D"2989" data-end=3D"2992">
Works great for backend/libs. Needs flags sometimes. Some orgs dislike =E2=
=80=9Cincomplete PRs=E2=80=9D.</p>
<h3 data-start=3D"3082" data-end=3D"3154">Option 2: <strong data-start=3D"3=
096" data-end=3D"3115">Vertical slices</strong> (harder, but best for stric=
t cultures)</h3>
<p data-start=3D"3155" data-end=3D"3209">Each PR delivers a small end-to-en=
d feature increment:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"3210" data-end=3D"3339">
<li data-start=3D"3210" data-end=3D"3339">
<p data-start=3D"3212" data-end=3D"3339">endpoint + minimal logic + tests +=
 docs, repeated 3=E2=80=935 times<br>
Rarely needs flags. Much harder to infer automatically from a diff.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"3341" data-end=3D"3453"><strong data-start=3D"3341" data-e=
nd=3D"3359">My blunt take:</strong> start with <strong data-start=3D"3371" =
data-end=3D"3382">layered</strong> for MVP, but add an enterprise setting: =
=E2=80=9Cvertical slicing mode=E2=80=9D later.</p>
<hr data-start=3D"3455" data-end=3D"3458">
<h2 data-start=3D"3460" data-end=3D"3504">Questions (you can answer in 1 li=
ne each)</h2>
<ol data-start=3D"3505" data-end=3D"3891">
<li data-start=3D"3505" data-end=3D"3653">
<p data-start=3D"3508" data-end=3D"3653">In your strict-review target, are =
<strong data-start=3D"3542" data-end=3D"3555">Draft PRs</strong> acceptable=
 as part of the stack (review later), or must every PR be ready for review =
immediately?</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3654" data-end=3D"3820">
<p data-start=3D"3657" data-end=3D"3820">Do you want the tool to <strong da=
ta-start=3D"3681" data-end=3D"3704">rewrite git history</strong> (split com=
mits / rebase) automatically, or should it only work from the final diff an=
d generate new commits itself?</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3821" data-end=3D"3891">
<p data-start=3D"3824" data-end=3D"3891">Do you want this to run as: <stron=
g data-start=3D"3852" data-end=3D"3865">local CLI</strong>, <strong data-st=
art=3D"3867" data-end=3D"3881">GitHub App</strong>, or both?</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start=3D"3893" data-end=3D"3923">Answer those and I=E2=80=99ll outl=
ine:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"3924" data-end=3D"4053" data-is-last-node=3D"" data-is-on=
ly-node=3D"">
<li data-start=3D"3924" data-end=3D"3982">
<p data-start=3D"3926" data-end=3D"3982">exact GitHub workflow (branches/PR=
 links/status checks),</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3983" data-end=3D"4006">
<p data-start=3D"3985" data-end=3D"4006">minimal architecture,</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"4007" data-end=3D"4053" data-is-last-node=3D"">
<p data-start=3D"4009" data-end=3D"4053" data-is-last-node=3D"">and what yo=
u can demo in 2 weeks vs 6 weeks.</p>
</li>
</ul></div></div></div></div><div class=3D"z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-st=
