-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start=3D"=
0" data-end=3D"25">Local CLI first is right.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"27" data-end=3D"78">GitHub App: what it buys you (and wha=
t it costs)</h2>
<h3 data-start=3D"79" data-end=3D"95">What you get</h3>
<ol data-start=3D"96" data-end=3D"127">
<li data-start=3D"96" data-end=3D"127">
<p data-start=3D"99" data-end=3D"127"><strong data-start=3D"99" data-end=3D=
"127">No tokens / no PAT drama</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"128" data-end=3D"247">
<li data-start=3D"128" data-end=3D"176">
<p data-start=3D"130" data-end=3D"176">Installs with scoped permissions per=
 repo/org.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"177" data-end=3D"247">
<p data-start=3D"179" data-end=3D"247">Easier sell in enterprises than =E2=
=80=9Cpaste a personal token into a CLI=E2=80=9D.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"2" data-start=3D"249" data-end=3D"278">
<li data-start=3D"249" data-end=3D"278">
<p data-start=3D"252" data-end=3D"278"><strong data-start=3D"252" data-end=
=3D"278">Server-side automation</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"279" data-end=3D"447">
<li data-start=3D"279" data-end=3D"335">
<p data-start=3D"281" data-end=3D"335">Webhooks: on review comment / reques=
ted changes / push</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"336" data-end=3D"395">
<p data-start=3D"338" data-end=3D"395">Auto-rebase downstream PRs immediate=
ly after PR i updates</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"396" data-end=3D"447">
<p data-start=3D"398" data-end=3D"447">Auto-update PR descriptions, labels,=
 stack status</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"3" data-start=3D"449" data-end=3D"484">
<li data-start=3D"449" data-end=3D"484">
<p data-start=3D"452" data-end=3D"484"><strong data-start=3D"452" data-end=
=3D"484">Better UX for strict culture</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"485" data-end=3D"656">
<li data-start=3D"485" data-end=3D"537">
<p data-start=3D"487" data-end=3D"537">=E2=80=9CStack view=E2=80=9D dashboa=
rd (checks/approvals/blockers)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"538" data-end=3D"617">
<p data-start=3D"540" data-end=3D"617">Enforce rules: =E2=80=9Ceverything b=
elow top is draft=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9Cmax 8 PRs=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9Ctests req=
uired=E2=80=9D</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"618" data-end=3D"656">
<p data-start=3D"620" data-end=3D"656">CODEOWNERS-aware reviewer assignment=
</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"4" data-start=3D"658" data-end=3D"694">
<li data-start=3D"658" data-end=3D"694">
<p data-start=3D"661" data-end=3D"694"><strong data-start=3D"661" data-end=
=3D"694">Multi-user / OSS friendliness</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"695" data-end=3D"855">
<li data-start=3D"695" data-end=3D"778">
<p data-start=3D"697" data-end=3D"778">Maintainers don=E2=80=99t need contr=
ibutors to run your CLI to keep the stack consistent.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"779" data-end=3D"855">
<p data-start=3D"781" data-end=3D"855">Works even if contributor disappears=
; the app can keep rebasing/repairing.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"857" data-end=3D"874">What it costs</h3>
<ol data-start=3D"875" data-end=3D"912">
<li data-start=3D"875" data-end=3D"912">
<p data-start=3D"878" data-end=3D"912"><strong data-start=3D"878" data-end=
=3D"912">Security + compliance overhead</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"913" data-end=3D"1051">
<li data-start=3D"913" data-end=3D"972">
<p data-start=3D"915" data-end=3D"972">You now store code access (even if y=
ou don=E2=80=99t store code).</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"973" data-end=3D"1051">
<p data-start=3D"975" data-end=3D"1051">Enterprises will ask about SOC2, da=
ta retention, hosting region, audit logs.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"2" data-start=3D"1053" data-end=3D"1082">
<li data-start=3D"1053" data-end=3D"1082">
<p data-start=3D"1056" data-end=3D"1082"><strong data-start=3D"1056" data-e=
nd=3D"1082">Operational complexity</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"1083" data-end=3D"1173">
<li data-start=3D"1083" data-end=3D"1141">
<p data-start=3D"1085" data-end=3D"1141">Hosting, uptime, retries, rate lim=
its, webhook delivery.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1142" data-end=3D"1173">
<p data-start=3D"1144" data-end=3D"1173">You=E2=80=99re a service company n=
ow.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"3" data-start=3D"1175" data-end=3D"1201">
<li data-start=3D"1175" data-end=3D"1201">
<p data-start=3D"1178" data-end=3D"1201"><strong data-start=3D"1178" data-e=
nd=3D"1201">Permission friction</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"1202" data-end=3D"1295">
<li data-start=3D"1202" data-end=3D"1295">
<p data-start=3D"1204" data-end=3D"1295">Some orgs won=E2=80=99t install ap=
ps easily, but they=E2=80=99ll allow a CLI with their existing auth flow.</=
p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1297" data-end=3D"1463"><strong data-start=3D"1297" data-e=
nd=3D"1312">Blunt take:</strong> CLI wins for MVP + early adopters. GitHub =
App becomes necessary once you want =E2=80=9Cself-healing stacks=E2=80=9D w=
ithout the developer constantly running commands.</p>
<hr data-start=3D"1465" data-end=3D"1468">
<h2 data-start=3D"1470" data-end=3D"1530">Your workflow choice (=E2=80=9Cli=
near review; only top PR ready=E2=80=9D)</h2>
<p data-start=3D"1531" data-end=3D"1572">Good. This matches strict-review r=
eality.</p>
<p data-start=3D"1574" data-end=3D"1688"><strong data-start=3D"1574" data-e=
nd=3D"1583">Rule:</strong> PR1 =3D Ready for review, PR2..PRn =3D Draft.<br=
 data-start=3D"1625" data-end=3D"1628">
When PR1 merges, PR2 flips to Ready, PR3..n stay Draft, etc.</p>
<p data-start=3D"1690" data-end=3D"1745">That avoids reviewers looking at c=
ode that might churn.</p>
<hr data-start=3D"1747" data-end=3D"1750">
<h2 data-start=3D"1752" data-end=3D"1801">How layered stack should behave (=
your default)</h2>
<ul data-start=3D"1802" data-end=3D"1970">
<li data-start=3D"1802" data-end=3D"1862">
<p data-start=3D"1804" data-end=3D"1862">Layered stack always, <strong data=
-start=3D"1826" data-end=3D"1849">unless diff is tiny</strong> =E2=86=92 si=
ngle PR.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1863" data-end=3D"1934">
<p data-start=3D"1865" data-end=3D"1934">=E2=80=9CTiny=E2=80=9D heuristic: =
e.g. &lt;300 LOC changed and &lt;=3D5 files (configurable).</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1935" data-end=3D"1970">
<p data-start=3D"1937" data-end=3D"1970">Stack size cap: default 5, max 8.<=
/p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start=3D"1972" data-end=3D"1975">
<h2 data-start=3D"1977" data-end=3D"2010">CLI design that actually works</h=
2>
<h3 data-start=3D"2011" data-end=3D"2023">Commands</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"2024" data-end=3D"2521">
<li data-start=3D"2024" data-end=3D"2123">
<p data-start=3D"2026" data-end=3D"2123"><code data-start=3D"2026" data-end=
=3D"2042">vibestack plan</code><br data-start=3D"2042" data-end=3D"2045">
Analyzes diff + transcript, proposes stack (PR titles + file lists + order)=
.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2124" data-end=3D"2196">
<p data-start=3D"2126" data-end=3D"2196"><code data-start=3D"2126" data-end=
=3D"2143">vibestack apply</code><br data-start=3D"2143" data-end=3D"2146">
Creates commits/branches for each slice locally.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2197" data-end=3D"2292">
<p data-start=3D"2199" data-end=3D"2292"><code data-start=3D"2199" data-end=
=3D"2215">vibestack push</code><br data-start=3D"2215" data-end=3D"2218">
Pushes branches + opens GitHub PRs. Marks only top as Ready, rest Draft.</p=
>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2293" data-end=3D"2423">
<p data-start=3D"2295" data-end=3D"2423"><code data-start=3D"2295" data-end=
=3D"2311">vibestack sync</code><br data-start=3D"2311" data-end=3D"2314">
After coder fixes PR1 from review, rebases PR2..n, updates PR bodies, re-ru=
ns checks locally if configured.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2424" data-end=3D"2521">
<p data-start=3D"2426" data-end=3D"2521"><code data-start=3D"2426" data-end=
=3D"2442">vibestack next</code><br data-start=3D"2442" data-end=3D"2445">
After PR1 merged, flips PR2 from Draft =E2=86=92 Ready, rebases remaining o=
n main.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"2523" data-end=3D"2567">Key constraint: =E2=80=9Cdon=E2=
=80=99t change semantics=E2=80=9D</h3>
<p data-start=3D"2568" data-end=3D"2621">So the tool should only do <strong=
 data-start=3D"2595" data-end=3D"2620">mechanical operations</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"2622" data-end=3D"2804">
<li data-start=3D"2622" data-end=3D"2650">
<p data-start=3D"2624" data-end=3D"2650">move hunks between commits</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2651" data-end=3D"2668">
<p data-start=3D"2653" data-end=3D"2668">reorder commits</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2669" data-end=3D"2804">
<p data-start=3D"2671" data-end=3D"2804">rebase + conflict resolution (but =
only straightforward textual conflicts)<br>
If conflict is non-trivial =E2=86=92 stop and ask coder to resolve.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start=3D"2806" data-end=3D"2809">
<h2 data-start=3D"2811" data-end=3D"2868">One critical technical decision: =
how to split the diff</h2>
<p data-start=3D"2869" data-end=3D"2929">You=E2=80=99ll need a deterministi=
c method that reviewers can trust.</p>
<p data-start=3D"2931" data-end=3D"2956">For layered mode, I=E2=80=99d do:<=
/p>
<ol data-start=3D"2957" data-end=3D"2983">
<li data-start=3D"2957" data-end=3D"2983">
<p data-start=3D"2960" data-end=3D"2983">Classify files by role:</p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"2984" data-end=3D"3105">
<li data-start=3D"2984" data-end=3D"3023">
<p data-start=3D"2986" data-end=3D"3023"><code data-start=3D"2986" data-end=
=3D"3001">types/schemas</code> (proto/openapi/types)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3024" data-end=3D"3046">
<p data-start=3D"3026" data-end=3D"3046"><code data-start=3D"3026" data-end=
=3D"3032">core</code> (lib, domain)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3047" data-end=3D"3086">
<p data-start=3D"3049" data-end=3D"3086"><code data-start=3D"3049" data-end=
=3D"3062">integration</code> (routes/controllers/DI)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3087" data-end=3D"3096">
<p data-start=3D"3089" data-end=3D"3096"><code data-start=3D"3089" data-end=
=3D"3096">tests</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3097" data-end=3D"3105">
<p data-start=3D"3099" data-end=3D"3105"><code data-start=3D"3099" data-end=
=3D"3105">docs</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"2" data-start=3D"3106" data-end=3D"3132">
<li data-start=3D"3106" data-end=3D"3132">
<p data-start=3D"3109" data-end=3D"3132">Build dependency edges:</p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"3133" data-end=3D"3160">
<li data-start=3D"3133" data-end=3D"3160">
<p data-start=3D"3135" data-end=3D"3160">import graph, symbol refs</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"3" data-start=3D"3161" data-end=3D"3213">
<li data-start=3D"3161" data-end=3D"3198">
<p data-start=3D"3164" data-end=3D"3198">Slice by =E2=80=9Clowest dependenc=
y first=E2=80=9D</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3199" data-end=3D"3213">
<p data-start=3D"3202" data-end=3D"3213">Guardrails:</p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul data-start=3D"3214" data-end=3D"3377">
<li data-start=3D"3214" data-end=3D"3251">
<p data-start=3D"3216" data-end=3D"3251">keep refactor-only changes togethe=
r</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3252" data-end=3D"3306">
<p data-start=3D"3254" data-end=3D"3306">don=E2=80=99t split a function acr=
oss PRs unless unavoidable</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3307" data-end=3D"3377">
<p data-start=3D"3309" data-end=3D"3377">keep test changes adjacent to the =
behavior they test (policy toggle)</p>
</li>
</ul>
