-start=3D"0" data-end=3D"161">Cool. Then the core is: <strong data-start=3D=
"24" data-end=3D"115">an AI =E2=80=9Cdiff slicer=E2=80=9D agent that output=
s a commit/PR plan you can deterministically apply</strong>, with a hard ga=
te: <strong data-start=3D"135" data-end=3D"160">every PR must pass CI</stro=
ng>.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"163" data-end=3D"216">How the AI agent should split (prac=
tical approach)</h2>
<h3 data-start=3D"217" data-end=3D"240">Inputs to the agent</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"241" data-end=3D"434">
<li data-start=3D"241" data-end=3D"267">
<p data-start=3D"243" data-end=3D"267">full git diff (or patch)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"268" data-end=3D"343">
<p data-start=3D"270" data-end=3D"343">repo tree + key files (package.json/=
pyproject, test configs, CI workflow)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"344" data-end=3D"380">
<p data-start=3D"346" data-end=3D"380">dependency signals (imports graph)</=
p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"381" data-end=3D"434">
<p data-start=3D"383" data-end=3D"434">(optional) chat transcript for =E2=
=80=9Cintent labels=E2=80=9D only</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"436" data-end=3D"481">Agent output (must be machine-appli=
cable)</h3>
<p data-start=3D"482" data-end=3D"499">A JSON plan like:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"500" data-end=3D"778">
<li data-start=3D"500" data-end=3D"530">
<p data-start=3D"502" data-end=3D"530"><code data-start=3D"502" data-end=3D=
"509">stack</code>: ordered list of PRs</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"531" data-end=3D"778">
<p data-start=3D"533" data-end=3D"541">each PR:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"544" data-end=3D"778">
<li data-start=3D"544" data-end=3D"551">
<p data-start=3D"546" data-end=3D"551">title</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"554" data-end=3D"573">
<p data-start=3D"556" data-end=3D"573">rationale (short)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"576" data-end=3D"640">
<p data-start=3D"578" data-end=3D"640">file-level allocation AND hunk-level=
 allocation (patch ranges)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"643" data-end=3D"681">
<p data-start=3D"645" data-end=3D"681">required checks (commands / CI jobs)=
</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"684" data-end=3D"778">
<p data-start=3D"686" data-end=3D"778">=E2=80=9Csafety notes=E2=80=9D (e.g.=
, =E2=80=9Crequires feature flag=E2=80=9D =E2=86=92 but you=E2=80=99ll disa=
ble flags unless repo allows)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"780" data-end=3D"864">Then your CLI <strong data-start=3D"=
794" data-end=3D"805">applies</strong> this plan (creates new commits), run=
s tests, and iterates.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"866" data-end=3D"919">The non-negotiable constraint: =E2=
=80=9Ceach PR passes CI=E2=80=9D</h2>
<p data-start=3D"920" data-end=3D"958">That dictates your splitting strateg=
y:</p>
<h3 data-start=3D"960" data-end=3D"1001">Default layering that still passes=
 CI</h3>
<p data-start=3D"1002" data-end=3D"1121">You can=E2=80=99t do =E2=80=9Ctype=
s only=E2=80=9D if it breaks unused code or leaves dead paths. So each PR m=
ust be <strong data-start=3D"1094" data-end=3D"1120">independently coherent=
</strong>.</p>
<p data-start=3D"1123" data-end=3D"1175">For TS/Python, the safe layered te=
mplate is usually:</p>
<ol data-start=3D"1177" data-end=3D"1433">
<li data-start=3D"1177" data-end=3D"1334">
<p data-start=3D"1180" data-end=3D"1217"><strong data-start=3D"1180" data-e=
nd=3D"1217">Scaffolding that compiles + tests</strong></p>
<ul data-start=3D"1221" data-end=3D"1334">
<li data-start=3D"1221" data-end=3D"1257">
<p data-start=3D"1223" data-end=3D"1257">add new modules/classes but unused=
</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1261" data-end=3D"1283">
<p data-start=3D"1263" data-end=3D"1283">add types/interfaces</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1287" data-end=3D"1334">
<p data-start=3D"1289" data-end=3D"1334">add no-op wiring guarded by not be=
ing invoked</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1335" data-end=3D"1365">
<p data-start=3D"1338" data-end=3D"1365"><strong data-start=3D"1338" data-e=
nd=3D"1365">Core logic + unit tests</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1366" data-end=3D"1411">
<p data-start=3D"1369" data-end=3D"1411"><strong data-start=3D"1369" data-e=
nd=3D"1411">Integration wiring + integration tests</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1412" data-end=3D"1433">
<p data-start=3D"1415" data-end=3D"1433"><strong data-start=3D"1415" data-e=
nd=3D"1433">Docs / cleanup</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start=3D"1435" data-end=3D"1620">If adding unused code breaks lint =
rules (common in TS), PR1 must include whatever is needed to satisfy lint (=
exports, minimal usage, or config adjustments <em data-start=3D"1590" data-=
end=3D"1618">only if approved in review</em>).</p>
<h3 data-start=3D"1622" data-end=3D"1652">Hard rule to keep CI green</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1653" data-end=3D"1844">
<li data-start=3D"1653" data-end=3D"1727">
<p data-start=3D"1655" data-end=3D"1727">No PR may introduce failing tests,=
 broken typecheck, or lint violations.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1728" data-end=3D"1844">
<p data-start=3D"1730" data-end=3D"1844">If you can=E2=80=99t keep a slice =
green, the tool must <strong data-start=3D"1777" data-end=3D"1802">merge ad=
jacent slices</strong> until it is green (reducing stack depth).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1846" data-end=3D"1938">So your =E2=80=9Cmax stack size=E2=
=80=9D becomes <strong data-start=3D"1879" data-end=3D"1890">dynamic</stron=
g>: as many PRs as possible <em data-start=3D"1916" data-end=3D"1937">while=
 staying green</em>.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"1940" data-end=3D"1965">CLI architecture (MVP)</h2>
<h3 data-start=3D"1966" data-end=3D"1987"><code data-start=3D"1970" data-en=
d=3D"1987">vibestack split</code></h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1988" data-end=3D"2218">
<li data-start=3D"1988" data-end=3D"2136">
<p data-start=3D"1990" data-end=3D"2011">runs local analyzers:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"2014" data-end=3D"2136">
<li data-start=3D"2014" data-end=3D"2082">
<p data-start=3D"2016" data-end=3D"2082">TS: <code data-start=3D"2020" data=
-end=3D"2034">tsc --noEmit</code>, eslint config detection, jest/vitest det=
ection</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2085" data-end=3D"2136">
<p data-start=3D"2087" data-end=3D"2136">Python: <code data-start=3D"2095" =
data-end=3D"2103">pytest</code>, <code data-start=3D"2105" data-end=3D"2118=
">ruff/flake8</code>, <code data-start=3D"2120" data-end=3D"2126">mypy</cod=
e> detection</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2137" data-end=3D"2180">
<p data-start=3D"2139" data-end=3D"2180">computes import graph and change c=
lusters</p>
</li>
