<li data-start=3D"2835" data-end=3D"2913">
<p data-start=3D"2837" data-end=3D"2913">re-run <code data-start=3D"2844" d=
ata-end=3D"2852">verify</code> locally for each PR boundary (fast mode: onl=
y affected ones)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start=3D"2915" data-end=3D"2981">How the agent actually decides bo=
undaries (TS/Python specifics)</h2>
<h3 data-start=3D"2982" data-end=3D"3008">Signals that work well</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"3009" data-end=3D"3413">
<li data-start=3D"3009" data-end=3D"3075">
<p data-start=3D"3011" data-end=3D"3075"><strong data-start=3D"3011" data-e=
nd=3D"3032">import dependency</strong>: don=E2=80=99t put a file in PR2 if =
PR1 imports it</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3076" data-end=3D"3169">
<p data-start=3D"3078" data-end=3D"3169"><strong data-start=3D"3078" data-e=
nd=3D"3096">test ownership</strong>: tests should sit with the behavior the=
y validate (otherwise PRs go red)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3170" data-end=3D"3269">
<p data-start=3D"3172" data-end=3D"3269"><strong data-start=3D"3172" data-e=
nd=3D"3187">entrypoints</strong>: wiring changes last unless they=E2=80=99r=
e required to keep code referenced / lint clean</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"3270" data-end=3D"3413">
<p data-start=3D"3272" data-end=3D"3413"><strong data-start=3D"3272" data-e=
nd=3D"3293">migrations/schema</strong>: isolate only if you can keep everyt=
hing compatible; otherwise bundle with the minimal app changes that make te=
sts pass</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"3415" data-end=3D"3454">What you explicitly <em data-star=
t=3D"3439" data-end=3D"3451">should not</em> do</h3>
