<li data-start=3D"325" data-end=3D"395">
<p data-start=3D"327" data-end=3D"395">the actual <code data-start=3D"338" =
data-end=3D"344">run:</code> commands (npm/pnpm/yarn, pytest, ruff, mypy, e=
tc.)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"396" data-end=3D"456">
<p data-start=3D"398" data-end=3D"456">required status checks <em data-star=
t=3D"421" data-end=3D"433">implicitly</em> (whatever runs on PRs)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"458" data-end=3D"523">That=E2=80=99s enough to build a =E2=
=80=9CCI contract=E2=80=9D without a new config file.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"525" data-end=3D"549">The catch (important)</h2>
<p data-start=3D"550" data-end=3D"629">You can=E2=80=99t always <em data-st=
art=3D"567" data-end=3D"583">run CI locally</em> faithfully by just reading=
 workflows because:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"630" data-end=3D"883">
<li data-start=3D"630" data-end=3D"678">
<p data-start=3D"632" data-end=3D"678">secrets, OIDC, cloud creds, private =
registries</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"679" data-end=3D"725">
<p data-start=3D"681" data-end=3D"725">services (Postgres/Redis) spun up in=
 Actions</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"726" data-end=3D"803">
<p data-start=3D"728" data-end=3D"803">composite actions / reusable workflo=
ws / action wrappers that hide commands</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"804" data-end=3D"883">
<p data-start=3D"806" data-end=3D"883"><code data-start=3D"806" data-end=3D=
"827">pull_request_target</code> security weirdness (often won=E2=80=99t ru=
n the same code path)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"885" data-end=3D"919">So you have two enforcement modes:</=
p>
<h3 data-start=3D"921" data-end=3D"972">Mode A =E2=80=94 =E2=80=9CLocal equ=
ivalent=E2=80=9D (fast, best dev UX)</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"973" data-end=3D"1120">
<li data-start=3D"973" data-end=3D"990">
<p data-start=3D"975" data-end=3D"990">Parse workflows</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"991" data-end=3D"1019">
<p data-start=3D"993" data-end=3D"1019">Identify the test commands</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1020" data-end=3D"1082">
<p data-start=3D"1022" data-end=3D"1082">Run them locally (or via container=
s) <strong data-start=3D"1059" data-end=3D"1069">before</strong> creating P=
Rs</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1083" data-end=3D"1120">
<p data-start=3D"1085" data-end=3D"1120">If it fails, merge slices and retr=
y</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1122" data-end=3D"1190">This works great when workflows ar=
e basically <code data-start=3D"1168" data-end=3D"1178">npm test</code> / <=
code data-start=3D"1181" data-end=3D"1189">pytest</code>.</p>
<h3 data-start=3D"1192" data-end=3D"1262">Mode B =E2=80=94 =E2=80=9CCI is t=
he source of truth=E2=80=9D (always correct, slower loop)</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1263" data-end=3D"1499">
<li data-start=3D"1263" data-end=3D"1296">
<p data-start=3D"1265" data-end=3D"1296">Generate the stack PRs as Draft</p=
>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1297" data-end=3D"1321">
<p data-start=3D"1299" data-end=3D"1321">Let GitHub Actions run</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1322" data-end=3D"1403">
<p data-start=3D"1324" data-end=3D"1403">Only when PR1 is green do you prom=
ote it to =E2=80=9CReady=E2=80=9D; PR2..n remain Draft anyway</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1404" data-end=3D"1499">
<p data-start=3D"1406" data-end=3D"1499">If PRk fails, your tool revises th=
e slicing (merge PRk with PRk+1) and force-pushes the stack</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1501" data-end=3D"1614">This guarantees =E2=80=9Ceverythin=
g passes CI=E2=80=9D because CI literally decides. Downsides: slower iterat=
ion and more pushes.</p>
<p data-start=3D"1616" data-end=3D"1738"><strong data-start=3D"1616" data-e=
nd=3D"1641">Blunt recommendation:</strong> support both, default to A, auto=
-fallback to B when workflows look non-local (secrets/services).</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"1740" data-end=3D"1783">How the CLI should infer CI (conc=
retely)</h2>
<ol data-start=3D"1784" data-end=3D"2305">
<li data-start=3D"1784" data-end=3D"1817">
<p data-start=3D"1787" data-end=3D"1817">Scan <code data-start=3D"1792" dat=
a-end=3D"1817">.github/workflows/*.yml</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1818" data-end=3D"1908">
<p data-start=3D"1821" data-end=3D"1908">Pick workflows triggered on PRs (<=
code data-start=3D"1854" data-end=3D"1868">pull_request</code>, maybe <code=
 data-start=3D"1876" data-end=3D"1891">workflow_call</code> via PR workflow=
)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1909" data-end=3D"2198">
<p data-start=3D"1912" data-end=3D"1925">For each job:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"1929" data-end=3D"2198">
<li data-start=3D"1929" data-end=3D"2013">
<p data-start=3D"1931" data-end=3D"2013">collapse matrix to a =E2=80=9Cprim=
ary lane=E2=80=9D (e.g., ubuntu-latest, latest language version)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2017" data-end=3D"2198">
<p data-start=3D"2019" data-end=3D"2041">extract step commands:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"2047" data-end=3D"2198">
<li data-start=3D"2047" data-end=3D"2140">
<p data-start=3D"2049" data-end=3D"2140">Node: <code data-start=3D"2055" da=
ta-end=3D"2063">npm ci</code> / <code data-start=3D"2066" data-end=3D"2074"=
>pnpm i</code> / <code data-start=3D"2077" data-end=3D"2091">yarn install</=
code>, then <code data-start=3D"2098" data-end=3D"2108">npm test</code>, <c=
ode data-start=3D"2110" data-end=3D"2124">npm run lint</code>, <code data-s=
tart=3D"2126" data-end=3D"2140">tsc --noEmit</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2146" data-end=3D"2198">
<p data-start=3D"2148" data-end=3D"2198">Python: <code data-start=3D"2156" =
data-end=3D"2172">pip install -r</code>, <code data-start=3D"2174" data-end=
=3D"2182">pytest</code>, <code data-start=3D"2184" data-end=3D"2190">ruff</=
code>, <code data-start=3D"2192" data-end=3D"2198">mypy</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2199" data-end=3D"2251">
<p data-start=3D"2202" data-end=3D"2251">Build a minimal ordered command li=
st per language</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2252" data-end=3D"2305">
<p data-start=3D"2255" data-end=3D"2305">Use those as your =E2=80=9Cmust pa=
ss=E2=80=9D gates for each slice</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start=3D"2307" data-end=3D"2419">If it can=E2=80=99t confidently ex=
tract commands (composite actions / reusable workflows), mark =E2=80=9Cunkn=
own=E2=80=9D and go Mode B.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"2421" data-end=3D"2478">What =E2=80=9Conly what=E2=80=99s=
 available in the repo=E2=80=9D means for you</h2>
<p data-start=3D"2479" data-end=3D"2544">Perfect: the tool should never ass=
ume ruff/eslint/etc.<br data-start=3D"2533" data-end=3D"2536">
It just:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"2545" data-end=3D"2675">
<li data-start=3D"2545" data-end=3D"2584">
<p data-start=3D"2547" data-end=3D"2584">detects if they=E2=80=99re present=
/configured</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2585" data-end=3D"2621">
<p data-start=3D"2587" data-end=3D"2621">and/or reads what CI actually runs=
</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2622" data-end=3D"2675">
<p data-start=3D"2624" data-end=3D"2675">otherwise it only guarantees =E2=
=80=9Cbuild passes=E2=80=9D at best</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start=3D"2677" data-end=3D"2713">One decision you need to make now=
</h2>
<p data-start=3D"2714" data-end=3D"2783">When CI uses a big matrix (Node 18=
/20, Py 3.10/3.12), do you require:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"2784" data-end=3D"2921">
<li data-start=3D"2784" data-end=3D"2850">
<p data-start=3D"2786" data-end=3D"2850"><strong data-start=3D"2786" data-e=
nd=3D"2825">all matrix lanes green for every PR</strong> (strictest, slowes=
t), or</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"2851" data-end=3D"2921">
<p data-start=3D"2853" data-end=3D"2921"><strong data-start=3D"2853" data-e=
nd=3D"2908">a representative lane locally + all lanes on GitHub</strong> (p=
ractical)?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"2923" data-end=3D"2982">I=E2=80=99d do: representative lan=
e locally, full matrix on GitHub.</p>
<h2 data-start=3D"2984" data-end=3D"3020">Next step: pick your MVP behavior=
</h2>
<p data-start=3D"3021" data-end=3D"3071">I=E2=80=99ll propose an MVP spec i=
